{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Review","itemReviewed":{"@id":"/trail/us/washington/mailbox-peak-old-trail","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Mailbox Peak (Old) Trail","address":{"@type":"PostalAddress","addressLocality":"North Bend, Washington, United States"}},"reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"reviewBody":"Hiked up and down the old trail on 12/27. There were still several spots in the upper parking lot when I got there around mid-day on a Saturday. Bathrooms at the trail were open. 

There were patchy areas of snow on the trail starting around 1600 feet. I put microspikes on at 2000 feet. Consistent packed snow on the trail around 2500 feet. 2-3 inches of snow on trail after the talus field. Ran into several people carrying snowshoes but definitely not needed today. 

Pretty clear day so we had great views from the top. Total time 3h58m","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Janvi S","url":"/members/janvi-shah"}}

{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Review","itemReviewed":{"@id":"/trail/us/washington/mount-washington","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Mount Washington Trail","address":{"@type":"PostalAddress","addressLocality":"North Bend, Washington, United States"}},"reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":4},"reviewBody":"01/09/2026: Giving the trail a four star as it felt like an obstacle course with so many trees down and snow constantly falling from the branches, but wow, totally worth it! Snowshoes were needed about 3 miles in, shortly after the wooden fence. That’s where I caught up to a group breaking trail, which helped a ton.

As of today, there’s a solid track in, but still plenty of deep snow, the base path is set though. And the views up top? Stunning. My second time at the summit and once again got lucky with blue sky and baller views of Mount Rainier.
","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"M P","url":"/members/m-perez-2"}}

{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Review","itemReviewed":{"@id":"/trail/us/washington/mcclellan-butte-trail","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"McClellan Butte Trail","address":{"@type":"PostalAddress","addressLocality":"North Bend, Washington, United States"}},"reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":4},"reviewBody":"Parking lot is closed so you’ll either have to park at a lot across the highway or along the street. 

Hike overall was a lot of fun. Spikes are a must. I managed without hiking poles. The short scramble to the top was completely dry as of today 2/4. Unreal views out to Rainier. 

Also clocked in a little over 12 miles, not the 10 shown.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Aaron Best","url":"/members/aaron-best-5"}}

{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Review","itemReviewed":{"@id":"/trail/us/washington/grand-prospect-via-rattlesnake-mountain-trail","@type":"LocalBusiness","name":"Grand Prospect via Rattlesnake Mountain Trail","address":{"@type":"PostalAddress","addressLocality":"North Bend, Washington, United States"}},"reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":5},"reviewBody":"Very pretty forest walk! Great well maintained trail with a super gentle incline. PERFECT for running, up and down.

Took our two pups and had a ton of fun in the mist and rain. Couldn’t see anything at the top and went over to west peak to also see nothing but mist. Was super quiet and empty outside of a group of trail runners! We came back super drenched as it rained all hike long, with decently strong wind lol. Big parking lot (40 cars), and this trail is hikers only/dogs.

Highly recommend as a nice recovery hike and forest bathing experience…","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"AllTrails User","url":"/members/alltrails-user-51393610"}}
